Some of my favorite decor ideas for holiday hosting 🎀 to save for later

* ribbons on (thrifted) glasses
* greenery (foraged branches, leaves or trader joes greens) for the table
* a few yards from the fabric store = your new favorite tablecloth
* bunched tulle as a table runner—sparkly is my fave ✨
* candles in front of a mirror to amplify light 
* cutie place cards, @maudeandmay’s ofc
* cake stands to stack desserts 🍰 
* ribbons on candle holders and flowers arrangements, no rules! More bows!

my favorite tables of 2023 + lil ideas to save for 2024

* summer solstice for @anthropologie - find a reason to celebrate *anything*
* @fikyfikywines dinner - crayons + paper on the table !! 🖍️ & pomegranates, grapes and lemons make for chic table decor
* my bday dinner - thrifted plates are elite
* @maudeandmay summer party - where my bow fixation began 🎀 a signature cocktail is such a cute touch
* house warming with @hillhouse - for indoor parties, hanging fabric makes for a beautiful backdrop
* galentines tea party - tiny cakes, painted candle sticks and cohosting are more fun 🫖 @amelia.edmondson 
* mojo dojo barbie dream house party beer pong table - sometimes it’s not aesthetic, it’s just fun :’)
* @shopnaiia jewelry dinner - silky fabric on the table looks rich & reflects candlelight 
* holiday @maudeandmay dinner - forage branches and hang them + whatever you want from the ceiling! more is more!
2023 🌪️⭐️❤️‍🔥 !!! move across the country, launch your dream brand, find joy, be joy, spread joy and (above all) hug the homies extra tight 💘💘 I love you all 🫶
